<tr><td align="left" class="newsCategory">Stratics Network Announcement - <font align="left" class="newsDate">10:33 AM PST</font></td></tr>
<tr><td valign="top" class="newsText"><p>Gamers have always been fighting to be recognized as intelligent individuals who are competitive. The fight started before a computer game existed, but the thoughts are still there, even with World of Warcraft and their billions of players. One of the first individuals to fight for video games, and those that play them was Raph Koster.</p><blockquote>Despite gaming being a bit more accepted in our culture, I think there's still plenty of resistance overall to regarding games as a medium comparable to any other. I also think there's a persistent notion within the industry that they don't deserve to be, and we need to get over that.</blockquote><p><a href = "http://www.stratics.com/content/exclusives/general/raph_koster.php">Read more</a> about his past, the present, and where gaming is going tomorrow.</p> </td></tr>
